Staff Reporter Police are appealing for help in tracing this man. (Supplied ) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Mfuleni police are appealing for help in tracing a man who went to work in Brackenfell but never arrived.&nbsp;According to a report from provncial police, John Mario Loock was last seen on Tuesday 2 May at about 07:30.&nbsp;Police spokesperson, Sergeant &nbsp;Noloyiso Rwexana, says Loock left his home to go to work in Brackenfell but never arrived. The clothing he wore at the time of his disappearance is not known.&nbsp;Anyone with information on where Loock may be is asked to call the investigating officer on 082 469 3247 or Mfuleni police on 021 909 9500.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.